latestPosts.caption:
BIG JAM 2023 HIPHOP 1 vs 1 CHAMPION,  Dancing in front of him is something I can’t express. I’m grateful receiving this title from the one and only @loosejointhiphopdance 🙏🏻. Sir, thankyou for coming to India and sharing your knowledge about Dance and culture. Top of it, Thankyou for appreciating my style 🙏 

This championship was won in 2018, and it is now in 2023. I will always be consistent with my training and learning, regardless of whether I win or lose “it’s the consistency for me” 
Everyone’s round went amazing, and we all performed splendidly. Let’s keep trying to put India on the map🇮🇳, love and respect to everyone in the community.
@bigdancecentre @atulbigdance  thank you so much for organising this great jam. ❤️🫂

17th July 2018 |
Nothing means more to me  than accepting this title from @majidk who I have always looked upto when it comes to Hip Hop freestyle.
 When I asked for feedback, I was super happy to hear his response "Keep doing what your doing and go share with others"

11th July 2018 | 
It all started with @realmakkhan 's call asking me what I wanted for my birthday. "Bhai tere birthday ke din Jam Kara raha hu tere favorite bande wala, par jeetna padega dekhle". That moment on I was goddamn excited to show majid what I had worked on these couple of years. It was simply thrilling to even think that I'd be dancing in front of him.
I ended up gifting myself the best birthday present I could ever give myself. What made me happier was I was in the finals with the one and only my favorite in this country, my brother @charliefrostcharlie Bhai. Whoever won, the title was coming home (Phir bhi mujhe jeetna Tha :p).
Representing @kunduhouseproject , 
hip hop one love 💓
Thanks to @bigdancecentre
 For making this possible and @realmakkhan  #hiphop #khp #freestyle #gillanation #india #delhi
